tip.text: Nice brunch place with good food and coffee. You can choose latte art as well when the shop is not busy.
Nice show and great staging.
Fried chicken and waffles for brunch/lunch!
Love the seasonal cilantro ramen!
Everything is delicious and we enjoyed rockfish and fresh Alaska king crab the most!
Nigiri is pretty fresh. Beef grill is good too. Not that crowded. Friendly service. Easy Parking nearby.
My favorite Sunday morning reading spot. Friendly service. Coffee art. Good music.

formattedAddress: 2128 Queen Anne Ave N (at W Boston Street)

tip.text: Oysters! Expensive but fresh and tasty. 4-6pm are their happy hours. Drink is good. Beef tartar is nice too.
Pizza is good, wine list is so so. We had dinner outside the restaurant in a hot summer day. Overall a good place to chill with friends.
Pretty much everything on the menu is great. Nice handmade fresh paste and fresh ingredient. Cocktails are tasty too. Relax place to hang out.
Ordered beet salad, oyster and pork belly. Food is well done with warm service. Good for a date night.
Beautiful dessert!
Very comfortable bed. A grand hotel with over 130 years history. They belong to SPG luxury collection so remember to lock your points. Good service.
Not sure why the rating is low. This hotel is very comfortable and trendy. We enjoyed the view from window. Clean room and soft bed. A total hidden gem. Nice location where u can walk around town.
Great Vietnamese food! Pho, spring roll and grill chicken lemongrass rice box are awesome!
We stopped by this little gem again. We ordered 4 courses tasting for €59. Pasta and halibut are great! Steak is a little hard. Service is A+!
It's next to ladyM! Grab a coffee and seat in the park next door to enjoy the sunshine. Blue bottle coffee latte is the best!
Xiaolongbao is very juicy and beef noodle is delicious. Good casual dinning place.
My new favorite spot in town! Next to staple and fancy but offers red meat. We had 4 courses meal - beet salad, trout, tuna, pork, pasta and chocolate cake. Everything is delicious!
Lots of delicious dishes here: rainbow Uni shooter, tuna tataki, tako wasabi. And kakuni bibimbap is the best!
Good the first time. Second time the fish isn't so fresh. We are not coming back anytime soon.
Nice latte here and comfy to work here.
Nice and cozy coffee shop with great latte. Love the industrial high ceiling with wooden deco. Free wifi. Around 20 people seating including counter.
Southern fried chicken is delicious. Chicken is a little dry. The shop is not big so expect to wait.
The hot pot is awesome. Good portion for two people.
Welcome to hotel California! You can walk around the block- this town is quiet and small. Margarita is quite good at the hotel bar.

formattedAddress: Benito Juárez s/n (e/ Morelos y Márquez de León)
location.crossStreet: e/ Morelos y Márquez de León

tip.text: Nice pinky hotel. We didn't stay here but went to take water taxi to the arch. $15 round trip.

formattedAddress: 23410 Cabo San Lucas, Baja California Sur

tip.text: Don't miss the Bon bons. Pasta is lovely. And the root beer pork belly!
Good for group. My friend had his birthday celebration here. Service is great. Love the scallop I had and the risotto.
As everyone mentions, the bacon wrapped date is Awesome. Love the mushroom also.
Nice seafood- oyster, fish and octopus! Nice cocktails too. Make sure you have a reservation, wait time could be very long.
Duck done perfect as well as the duck oil fries! Nice deco but a little noisy. Excellent service. Good for date or group.
Love the latte and deco here- very hard to find parking around though.
Probably the only Korean restaurant here but awesome! Love the hotpot, oxtail soup, and pretty much everything!
Foie gras is so awesome!
Asian Sunday morning to do!
Korean fusion done right. Love the steak lettuce wrap.

formattedAddress: 4012 Leary Way NW (41st & Leary Way NW)

tip.text: Pretty cool place to hangout with friends at late night. Drink is awesome. Food are quite unique from all over the places.
Good place to stop by with amazing view!. Very elegant coffee shop. Love everything here.
Super awesome and authentic Thaifood. Basil chicken with fried egg!
Very good coffee. They offer many types of crepe. Good stop on your way to Hana.
Love the acai bowl here. And the Bagel is awesome. Great start of the day.
Order two dozens! Fresh oyster is the best! And I tried the baked oyster- yummy as well.

venue.name: Taylor Shellfish Oyster Bar Queen Anne

tip.text: The Kobe beef is truly tender and I love the beets salad here. Very lovely restaurant for a casual dine out.
Best foie de pato I had in Seattle!
The chips and gua are really good! I had chicken thigh with rice, not oily at all. Rich in flavor.
Food and service are very good. Love the deco of this restaurant.
Loved everything about mammoth. Great trails and deep pow during the weekend we visited. Will be back!
Airport is very small but amazingly beautiful. It's so convenient that you can get on to slope within an hour. Take mammoth cab (not taxi). They are much cheaper.
Love the food here- we order three appetizer and one main. Quite good for two people. Don't miss Grill meat.
They don't offer latte here but coffee with milk is close enough. Pastry is so delicious!

formattedAddress: 5413 6th Ave NW (6th and NW Market St.)

tip.text: We came here another day for brunch. The Dan Dan noodle is epic!
We came here for brunch- food is awesome. The wait is long though. Try the poached egg and yogurt. Yummy.
Love the gyoza combo for lunch. This place could get vey crowded for lunch .
What a cool starbucks! Love the concept.

contact.facebookName: Starbucks Reserve Roastery and Tasting Room

tip.text: They have TV by the bar to play sports game. Burger is huge.
Neighborhood coffee place. Nice and cozy.
View from the coffee place. Awesome coffee and service. Good wifi.
Omakase by the courter is great. Chef is friendly.
That's a very huge burger! The wasabi source is amazing!
We stayed here for two nights this time - Luna and high moon. Super relax. Enjoyed the private hot tub as well.

contact.facebookName: Ten Thousand Waves Japanese Spa & Resort

tip.text: Tapas trio tastes great. Love this little gem near the square. Good to stop here for lunch.
Sunset is the best. Sunrise will be blocked by the mountain and park doesn't open till 7. If u drove over the entrance, be prepared to go through border checkpoint when return.

venue.name: White Sands National Monument - Interdune Boardwalk

tip.text: They serve blue coffee here!
Nice location and fancy office- the employee entrance is located at 8th Abe and 41st street.
Lunch special.

formattedAddress: 1368 W Pender St (btwn Broughton and Jervis)

tip.text: Brunch is awesome. This place can get quite crowded so come early.
Very nice boutique hotel.
super good!
Get the special Tonkatsu ramen!

contact.facebookName: らーめん山頭火 ／hokkaido ramen santouka

tip.text: The perfect neighborhood coffee shop! Coffee, fresh juice and waffles.
Great theater as the permanent home of academy awards. Happy that we hold an event here.
Ordered the bambu special- flavor of Southeast Asia!
Definitely my favorite coffee/breakfast spot in the city. Blue bottle is the best! Try the French toast also.
Awesome Japanese food- pork belly, mochi, scallop... They have many sake selections also.
At the top of Pompidou, get a reservation if you want seats by the window. Great view. At the pricy side.
One of my favorite museum now! I managed to catch Martial Raysse's temporary exhibition. What a great show.

venue.name: Pompidou Centre – National Museum of Modern Art (Centre Pompidou – Musée National d'Art Moderne)

tip.text: Nice cocktail. Interesting fusion Vietnamese food. Good for friends' hang out.
Best whiskey bar in town- rich menu and great atmosphere. They open after 8 pm- get in early to grab a seat.
Came here during sunset. The view is magnificent. We sit outside at the patio. Nice place to hang out with friends.
Ordered 5 courses tasting menu. Ingredient are fresh. Everything is delicious! Love the tomatoes! Remember to make reservation and they don't take table more than 5. I gave this little place a 10!
Love the nice garden inside of the hotel. Services are great. I got the room facing canal, what a nice view.
Nice Mexican food.
Great place to see sunset in San Diego.

formattedAddress: Sunset Cliffs Blvd (btwn Adair & Ladera St)

tip.text: This is the best sushi place we visited for a while. Amazed by the quality of seafood in San Diego. Fatty tuna, white tuna, salmon, shrimp, everything is great.
Brunch buffet with the view of San Diego bay. I agree that's the best place to dine on Sunday morning. $42 per person including crab, oyster, scallop, drink and etc. Never sober after brunch!
It's just magical. It has a very long beach line that directly facing the west towards Pacific Ocean. Where else do you need to find for a magnificent sunset!
Great to find this little quiet and elegant B&B two blocks from the beach. Though built years ago, rooms are well maintained. Staff are very friendly. Definitely coming back.
We went there on Sunday night, the wait is about 10 min around 8:30. Service is good. Soup is great but meat can be better. Great for a quick dinner.
No shelter for the driving range. But service is good.
No wifi. Always crowded. But the bakery is not bad. A good addition to fortyhands.
Flat white is the morning wake up call.

formattedAddress: 5307 Ballard Ave NW (at NW Vernon Pl)

tip.text: I went here for a happy hour on Friday afternoon with friends. Very cozy atmosphere. Try a flight and chill with friends.
Awesome spot, intimate place. Simple menu, fresh ingredient, awesome taste! Nothing would go wrong, just order anything. Love the open kitchen!

formattedAddress: 550 Green St (btwn Stockton St & Grant Ave)

tip.text: A quick stop if you are by the pike market
Nice brunch spot. They have big space in the back so the waiting wont be long. Very French restaurant. Good food.

Lovely brunch place. Brunch offer from Fri till Sun. Love the egg Benedict!
I ordered sausage with red pepper. Great pizza!
Nice brunch place. Not too crowded. Love the fat hen logo!
